00065 double Ricean::fadingFactor(const WirelessCommSignal& signal, 
00066    const NodeId& nodeId)
00067 {
00068    // This code is from the ns-2 module by Punnoose et al.
00069    // See their code and paper for details of the model.
00070 
00071    // MJM: I modified the model to compute a different fading
00072    // factor for each receiver to avoid having the same
00073    // fading factor globally for a given time instance.
00074    
00075    double maxFrequency = m_maxVelocity / signal.getWavelength();
00076    SimTime currentTime = Simulator::instance()->currentTime();
00077    double timeIndex = (currentTime.getTimeInSeconds() * 
00078       m_MAX_SAMPLE_RATE * (maxFrequency / m_MAX_DOPPLER_FREQUENCY));
00079    timeIndex = timeIndex - (m_NUMBER_OF_POINTS * 
00080       floor(timeIndex / m_NUMBER_OF_POINTS));
00081 
00082    // Envelope interpolation using Legendre polynomials
00083    int idx1 = static_cast<int>(floor(timeIndex));
00084    assert(idx1 >= 0 && idx1 < static_cast<int>(m_NUMBER_OF_POINTS));
00085 
00086    map<NodeId,int>::const_iterator p = m_nodeOffset.find(nodeId);
00087    if(p == m_nodeOffset.end()) {
00088       RandNumGeneratorPtr rand = 
00089          Simulator::instance()->getRandNumGenerator();
00090       m_nodeOffset[nodeId] = 
00091          rand->uniformInt(0, (m_NUMBER_OF_POINTS - 1));;
00092    }
00093    idx1 = (idx1 + m_nodeOffset[nodeId]) % m_NUMBER_OF_POINTS;
00094 
00095    int idx0 = (idx1 - 1 + m_NUMBER_OF_POINTS) % m_NUMBER_OF_POINTS;
00096    int idx2 = (idx1 + 1) % m_NUMBER_OF_POINTS;
00097    int idx3 = (idx1 + 2) % m_NUMBER_OF_POINTS;
00098 
00099    //double X1 = timeIndex - idx1;
00100    double X1 = timeIndex - floor(timeIndex);
00101    double X0 = X1 + 1.0;
00102    double X2 = X1 - 1.0;
00103    double X3 = X1 - 2.0;
00104 
00105    double interpolation1 =
00106       (m_GAUSSIAN_DATA1[idx0] * X1 * X2 * X3 / -6.0) +
00107       (m_GAUSSIAN_DATA1[idx1] * X0 * X2 * X3 * 0.5) +
00108       (m_GAUSSIAN_DATA1[idx2] * X0 * X1 * X3 * -0.5) +
00109       (m_GAUSSIAN_DATA1[idx3] * X0 * X1 * X2 / 6.0);
00110 
00111    double interpolation2 =
00112       (m_GAUSSIAN_DATA2[idx0] * X1 * X2 * X3 / -6.0) +
00113       (m_GAUSSIAN_DATA2[idx1] * X0 * X2 * X3 * 0.5) +
00114       (m_GAUSSIAN_DATA2[idx2] * X0 * X1 * X3 * -0.5) +
00115       (m_GAUSSIAN_DATA2[idx3] * X0 * X1 * X2 / 6.0);
00116 
00117    // The envelope multiplicative factor
00118    double numeratorTerm1 = interpolation1 + sqrt(2.0 * m_kParameter);
00119    double envelopeFactor = 
00120       (pow(numeratorTerm1, 2) + pow(interpolation2, 2)) / 
00121       (2.0 * (m_kParameter + 1));
00122 
00123    return envelopeFactor;
00124 }
